to the editor far more single mothers are taking jobs news article nov 5 underscores the need to increase low income families access to safe and reliable child care child care costs can easily account for one fifth of the income of these families leaving too little for other necessities and while there are now more child care subsidies focused on lowincome families research by the children 's defense fund finds that fewer than 20 percent of eligible families receive them the less reliable child care arrangements upon which many low income families depend can also disrupt their work efforts and undermine their prospects for getting ahead chauna brocht washington nov 6 2000 the writer is a policy analyst at the economic policy institute

